AMS <-> ACsoft integration Notes - 25. November 2012
-------------------------------------------------------------

Here are some notes on how to compile AMS with ACsoft enabled.
This documentation assumes that you're working on lxplus, or any AMS pcamsr0.cern.ch machine.

1. Checkout AMS software into $HOME/Software/AMS

2. Set environment variables
   > export AMSWD=$HOME/Software/AMS
   > export ACROOTSOFTWARE=/afs/cern.ch/exp/ams/Offline/AMSDataDir/v5.00/TRD
   > export ACROOTLOOKUPS=$ACROOTSOFTWARE/acroot/data
 
3. Compile AMS software
   > tcsh
   > cd $AMSWD/install
   > source amsvar
   > gmake all

4. Compile test program
  > cd $AMSWD/examples/trdqt
  > gmake

5. Run test program
  > cd $AMSWD/examples/trdqt
  > ./trdqt_example root://castorpublic.cern.ch///castor/cern.ch/ams/Data/AMS02/2011B/ISS.B620/pass4/1323073267.00000001.root?svcClass=amsuser
